questions.text: What is the sum \( (3-2i) + (-4+3i) \)?
questions.displayName: Add complex numbers
questions.feedback:
Step 1: Group real and imaginary parts
\( (3-2i) + (-4 + 3i) = (3-4) + (-2+3)i \)
Step 2: Evaluate real and imaginary parts
\( (3-4) + (-2+3)i = -1 + i \)

questions.text: What is the sum \( (2-3i) + (1+i) \)?
questions.displayName: Copy of Add/subtract complex numbers #5
questions.feedback:
Step 1: Group real and imaginary parts
\( (2-3i) + (1+i) = (2+1) + (-3+1)i \)
Step 2: Evaluate real and imaginary parts
\( (2+1) + (-3+1)i = 3 -2i \)

questions.displayName: Group real and imaginary parts
questions.text:
Group the real and imaginary parts of the expression:

\( (-1 + 5i) + (3 - 2i) \)

\( (3 + 4i) - (-2 + 3i) \)
questions.displayName: Subtract complex numbers
questions.feedback:
Step 1: Group real and imaginary parts
\( (3+4i)-(-2+3i) = (3--2) + (4-3)i \)
Step 2: Evaluate real and imaginary parts
\( (3--2) + (4-3)i = 5 + i \)
